name: Amir Chakhmagh Historical Mosque
description: The Amir Chakhmaq Mosque, also known as Dahouk mosque, is a historical mosque from the Timurid era in Yazd, in Iran. It was built on orders of Jalal ed-Din Amir Chakhmaq Shami, who was the governor of Yazd and a general of Shahrukh Mirza. The mosque was completed in 1438.
